# .dockerignore
# Excludes files from the Docker build context (what gets sent to the Docker
# daemon when building an image). Keeps builds fast and, more importantly,
# keeps real secrets out of any image layer.

# Local secrets - .env holds real DB_PASSWORD/JWT_SECRET values; must never
# be baked into an image. Real config is passed in at container run time via
# environment variables instead (see docker-compose.yml).
.env
.env.example

# Build output - regenerated fresh inside the container by the build stage;
# copying a stale local build in would be both wasteful and potentially wrong.
target/

# Version control - irrelevant to running the app, and .git can be large.
.git
.gitignore

# IDE/editor metadata - machine-specific, not part of the app itself.
.idea/
.vscode/
*.iml

# OS junk
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Docker's own files - no reason for the build context to include itself.
Dockerfile
docker-compose.yml
.dockerignore
